    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 2 shows immuno-EM on GIPC1 in rodent hippocampus, which is found both in the pre- and post-synapse. Fig2c shows clear immunoreactivity by light microscopy in wild type which is not present in the Gipc1 null, indicating that the antibody is specific. Fig 2f and g show immunoreactivity in the presynapse by DAB and immunogold methods respectively. Panels e and h show immunoreactivity in the postsynaptic compartment with the same two methods.. Experimental description: The immuno-EM was done on rat and mouse (M&M \"Adult male mice or Sprague-Dawley rats were anesthetized, perfused, and processed for light or electron microscopy as described previously\") the panels in Fig2 e-i are not further specified \"Ultrastructural analysis of GIPC1 in adult rodent hippocampus.\"\n\n8/7/2017 Pim\n- The lack of species information in Fig.2e-i is problematic. I have contacted the authors (moses.chao@med.nyu.edu; email dd 8/7/2017) for additional information. Answer: \"For Fig.2 the species of the tissues used in panels e-i, Images (e, f, g, h) are rat. Image (i) is mouse.\" I have made annotation to rat species.",
